:To the best of my knowledge, the ''only'' change to the XCG-20 to turn it into the XC-123 was the addition of engines - the C-123's fuel tanks were even mounted inside the nacelles (and were jettisonable in case of fire -!). I assume the XC-123A with its jets had internal fuel tanks (in the cargo hold?), but the airframe itself was unchanged in any significant fashion. (To the point where one source claims ''"every C-123 built had provision for a tow hook mounted in the nose"''!). - [[User:The Bushranger|The Bushranger]] <sub>[[User talk:The Bushranger|Return fire]]</sub><small><sup>[[User:The Bushranger/Pages Created|''Flank speed'']]</sup></small> 22:30, 2 December 2010 (UTC)

